trend_summary: Across the series, the central town expands modestly with new fringe neighborhoods and a few industrial lots. Radial roads thicken, improving regional access. Farmland still dominates, though many fields merge or rotate crops, and scattered woodland patches grow, especially near rivers. Despite change, the county remains largely rural.
notable_changes: Gradual outward growth of the main settlement, adding low-rise housing on all sides.
Establishment of small industrial/commercial plots south-east of the town core.
Widening and straightening of key arterial roads, plus a new bypass segment.
Consolidation of agricultural parcels, reducing hedgerows and creating larger fields.
Incremental woodland gain along northern and river-edge zones, hinting at regreening efforts.
